        <mxCell id="note1" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;fontColor=#000000;fontSize=11;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=6;dashed=1;" value="Notes&lt;br&gt;• Tascam 2400 = mixer + USB interface (replaces Scarlett)&lt;br&gt;• Palmer Pan 16 MERGES MPC2500 + MPC3000 outs 1-8 → Tascam ch 1-8; both stay patched, one MPC active at a time&lt;br&gt;• Mixdown outboard: SPL inserts ch 1-4 (per drum); DBX on drum subgroup 1; Lexicon/Alesis on aux&lt;br&gt;• Re-sample sends (aux): aux 1 → S950, aux 2 → MPC2500, aux 3 → MPC3000&lt;br&gt;• Returns: S950 L → ch 9 (dry), S950 R → Vermona → ch 10 (filtered), Lexicon → ch 11, Alesis → ch 12&lt;br&gt;• Stem-split: S950 plays back → ch 10 via Vermona (HP/LP/BP passes) → re-sample into 2500/3000 pads&lt;br&gt;• MPC2000 retired (inactive) — returns as source-sampler (ch 19/20) when desk space allows&lt;br&gt;• USB carries stereo mix (Pass 1) + per-channel stems (Pass 2)&lt;br&gt;• Dashed yellow = outboard aux/insert routing&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
